        "In this notebook, we will use State College weather data from 2000-2020 to put together a graph. In the graph we will be analyzing and visualizing what month it snows the most in State College on average. This is useful knowledge for college students so they can prepare ahead of time for the snow. Along with the initial graph will be three more graphs. These additional three graphs will represent a good way to encode the data, a bad way to encode the data, and a visually unpleasing way to encode the data for the students to view and analyze."
