        "We decided that a bar graph was the best to represent the data because it represented the data easily. The color we used was a bright blue, which draws the eye and is from the cool spectrum of colors. The cool spectrum was used because people easily associate cool colors with the weather, such as the snow. The blue we used was not from the default colormap which helps interest the onlooker. The data is chunked together in a way that makes it easy to analyze and process quickly. Finally, the intervals of 0.1 makes it easy to see what inch level the average snowfall is."
